Package: apa.cor
Title: Generate a Correlation Matrix in APA Style
Version: 0.0.0.98
Authors@R: 
    person("George", "Gunnesch-Luca", , "george.gunnesch-luca@fau.de", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7563-8020"))
Description: This function is designed to be a fast way of creating a correlation matrix from a dataframe that includes the needed variables. It also produces means, standard deviations and NHS significance tests at various levels, with an export function for the clipboard.
